1
00:00:20,541 --> 00:00:25,208
(序幕)

2
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:37,750
(1857年,极北方)

3
00:00:54,791 --> 00:00:56,250
船长!
Captain!

4
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:03,375
船长!
Captain!

5
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:05,583
我们能谈谈吗?
Can we talk?

6
00:01:13,166 --> 00:01:14,708
我们非突破冰阵不可
Hmm.
We must break through the ice.

7
00:01:15,208 --> 00:01:17,000
大伙们又饿又累
The men are hungry and exhausted.

8
00:01:18,083 --> 00:01:20,833
照这速度下去,后果不堪设想
We cannot keep up this pace without consequence.

9
00:01:25,291 --> 00:01:26,708
大家听好!
Listen up, men!

10
00:01:27,875 --> 00:01:30,249
我们进度越落后
The more we delay the labor,

11
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:32,666
冰就会黏得越紧
the firmer the grasp of the ice will become.

12
00:01:33,458 --> 00:01:34,750
继续干活
The work continues.

13
00:01:35,291 --> 00:01:36,208
各组轮流工作
Rotate each group.

14
00:01:36,791 --> 00:01:37,958
船长,恕我直言
Sir, with respect...

15
00:01:38,541 --> 00:01:39,999
大伙们需要你的保证
The men need assurances.

16
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,040
保证?
Assurances?

17
00:01:41,041 --> 00:01:45,082
是,船一脱困就返回圣彼得堡
Yes, that we will head back to St. Petersburg once we free the ship.

18
00:01:45,083 --> 00:01:47,540
他们认为船体撑不了远航,想知道...
They don't think we'll be seaworthy for long and they want to know--

19
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:49,125
听好!
Listen up!

20
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:55,874
你们和这位军官都不该心有旁念
It is neither your place, nor the officer here, to think anything...

21
00:01:55,875 --> 00:01:59,749
既然接下任务,就要完成目标
We signed up for a mission and we will see it to completion.

22
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,749
我们一定会抵达北极
We will reach the North Pole.

23
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:03,125
懂了吗?
Is it understood?

24
00:02:38,875 --> 00:02:40,750
发生爆炸,船长
An explosion, Captain.

25
00:02:43,541 --> 00:02:45,083
大约三公里外
About two miles away.

26
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:53,083
带几个人一起去
Get the men.

27
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,332
雪橇犬毫发无伤
The sled dogs are unharmed.

28
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,082
那这些血从何而来?
Then where does all this blood come from?

29
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:16,583
在这边,船长!
Over here, Captain!

30
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:20,541
有个人受伤,他严重失血
A wounded man, he's lost a lot of blood.

31
00:03:23,125 --> 00:03:26,041
肩膀有伤,他的腿断了
Wound to the shoulder, his leg is broken.

32
00:03:27,125 --> 00:03:28,665
他被熊攻击吗?
Bear attack?

33
00:03:28,666 --> 00:03:29,874
应该不是,船长
I don't think so, Captain.

34
00:03:29,875 --> 00:03:31,708
拉森,帮我脱掉他的靴子
Larsen, help me with his boot.

35
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:43,666
是义肢
A prosthetic leg.

36
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:53,125
把他放到木板上
Put him on the board.

37
00:03:56,041 --> 00:03:57,458
快点!立刻回船上!
Hurry! To the ship! Now!

38
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,583
拉森,那东西过来了
Larsen, that thing is coming.

39
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,458
步枪就位!
Ready the rifles!

40
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,875
听我口令
On my command.

41
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,250
瞄准!
Aim!

42
00:04:22,791 --> 00:04:24,500
射击!
Fire!

43
00:04:35,791 --> 00:04:36,791
下一组!
Next group!

44
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:41,791
射击!
Fire!

45
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,458
全体上船!
All to the ship!!

46
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:19,332
我们带上船的人在哪里?
Where is that man we brought onboard?

47
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:20,250
他人呢?
Where?

48
00:05:20,875 --> 00:05:22,875
那是什么鬼东西?牠想要什么?
What is that thing? What does it want?

49
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:35,333
把他交给我!
Bring him to me!

50
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:50,833
雷筒,拉森,去拿雷筒!
The blunderbuss. Larsen, get the blunderbuss!

51
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:03,416
维多
Victor.

52
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,375
维多!
Victor!

53
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:20,791
我干掉牠了
I killed it.

54
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:22,750
我干掉牠了
I killed it.

55
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:37,082
牠还活着!
It's still alive!

56
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:38,207
梯子!
Ladder!

57
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:39,625
把梯子拉上来!
Pull up the ladder!

58
00:06:54,166 --> 00:06:58,875
把他交给我!
Bring him to me!

59
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:18,540
剩下几发子弹?
How many shots are left?

60
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:20,540
一发,但杀不了牠
One, but it can't kill it.

61
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:21,583
我知道
I know.

62
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:23,875
我不是要瞄准牠
I'm not aiming for him.

63
00:08:15,625 --> 00:08:18,875
鸦片酊能减轻疼痛,喝吧
Laudanum, to ease the pain. Drink it. Drink it.

64
00:08:24,208 --> 00:08:25,624
我在哪里?
Where am I?

65
00:08:25,625 --> 00:08:27,332
这是丹麦皇家船舰,地平线号
You are on the Royal Danish ship, Horisont.

66
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,249
我是安德森船长,这是乌德森医生
I'm Captain Anderson. This is Dr. Udsen.

67
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:31,375
牠杀了多少船员?
How many of your men did it kill?

68
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:34,749
六个
Six.

69
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,208
牠会回来夺走更多条人命
It will come back and kill many more.

70
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:42,249
必要时会把你们都杀光 除非你们把我交给牠
All of you, if necessary, unless you deliver me to it.

71
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:43,457
不用,牠已经死了
No, no. It's gone.

72
00:08:43,458 --> 00:08:45,499
牠沉入冰冷海水中,已经死了
It sank in the freezing waters. It's dead.

73
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,125
牠没死!
No, it is not!

74
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:48,833
牠不会死
It cannot die.

75
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:51,458
我曾经想摧毁牠
I have tried to destroy it.

76
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,416
信不信由你们
Whether you believe me or not,

77
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,250
牠会回来...找我
it will come back... for me.

78
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:02,125
到了那时
And when it does,

79
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:06,665
你得保证要把我放在冰原上
you must promise that you will put me out on the ice

80
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:07,916
让牠将我带走
and let it take me.

81
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:10,125
求求你
Please.

82
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:12,625
那是何等怪物?
What manner of creature is that?

83
00:09:14,166 --> 00:09:17,125
究竟是何等恶魔创造牠的?
What manner of devil made him?

84
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:20,000
是我
I did.

85
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:23,000
是我
I did.

86
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:25,500
是我创造他的
I made him.

87
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:32,375
我已决心让我恶行的回忆随我消亡
I had determined that the memory of my evils should die with me.

88
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:34,166
修好了
It's ready.

89
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:37,791
我要说的话有些是事实
Some of what I will tell you is fact.

90
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:42,790
有些不是,但全都千真万确
Some is not, but it is all true.

91
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:44,833
我名叫维多
My name is Victor.

92
00:09:45,375 --> 00:09:46,833
维多弗兰肯斯坦
Victor Frankenstein.

93
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:51,333
这是我父亲为我取的名字
It was my father who gave me that name.

94
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:53,332
你知道这名字的意义吗?
Do you know what it means?

95
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:55,791
我知道,征服者
I believe I do, yes. Conqueror.

96
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:57,749
最大的赢家
One that wins it all.

97
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,916
对,一切都从他而起
Yes. It all started with him.

98
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:01,458
我的父亲
My father.

99
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:05,333
还有我的母亲
And my mother.

100
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:10,457
维多!

101
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:12,582
(第一部:维多的故事)
Victor!

102
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:13,500
维多!
Victor!

103
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:17,250
维多!
Victor!

104
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:24,416
快下来,你父亲快到家了
Come down, your father is arriving.
Maman? Maman?

105
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:30,666
我在这里,妈妈
I'm here, Mother.

106
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:35,291
我在这里
I'm here.

107
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:41,541
我父亲是男爵,也是卓越的外科医生
My father was a baron and a preeminent surgeon.

108
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:44,665
他娶我的母亲主要是图一时之便
He had married my mother largely out of convenience,

109
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:47,749
因为她的嫁妆可观且血统高贵
as her dowry was considerable and her lineage noble.

110
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:53,208
我父亲便得以保住爵位和家族庄园
It furnished my father with the means to preserve his rank and family estate.

111
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:08,040
他经常不在我们身边
He was absent from our lives,

112
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:11,041
但只要回家 从上到下都对他唯命是从
but when he came home, the entire household bent to his will.

113
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:12,666
克莱儿,亲爱的
Claire, dear.

114
00:11:13,166 --> 00:11:14,375
而其他时候...
The rest of the time...

115
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:16,165
维多
Victor.

116
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:17,249
父亲
Father.

117
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:19,708
其他时候,母亲由我独占
The rest of the time, Mother was mine.

118
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:29,666
不行,拿过来
No, bring that here.

119
00:11:37,041 --> 00:11:39,165
肉里的盐分会滋养血液
The salts in the meat will enrich your blood,

120
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:40,541
母子均能受益
as well as the baby's.

121
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:42,833
记得你是一人吃两人补吗?
You eat for two, remember?

122
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:55,083
吃啊
Go on.

123
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:57,291
这很营养
It's nutritious.

124
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:04,500
守护天使
Guardian angel.

125
00:12:05,208 --> 00:12:06,500
贴心的伴侣
Sweet companion.

126
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:09,416
请长相左右,勿弃我而去
Stand by my side and do not leave me.

127
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:13,166
以你的斗篷荫庇我,以及...
Under your mantle,
shelter me, and...

128
00:12:15,583 --> 00:12:18,624
他们争论不休,隔着墙也听得到
I would hear them through the wall, arguing incessantly,

129
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:23,041
互相叫骂,吵着家产、庄园...还有我
yelling at each other about wealth, estate... and me.

130
00:12:23,875 --> 00:12:26,541
他们的声音让我恐惧不已
Their voices filled me with fear.

131
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:32,083
Maman?

132
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:35,208
Maman?

133
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:48,207
他鄙视我们母子
The man despised us both.

134
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:52,125
我们乌黑的发丝、深黝的双眸
Our raven black hair, our deep, dark eyes.

135
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:56,790
连我们的寡言,有时神经质的性格
Even our quiet, at times nervous disposition

136
00:12:56,791 --> 00:12:59,583
似乎也会让他恼怒无比
seemed to exasperate him to no end.

137
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:02,874
尽你所能地正确说出
List as accurately as you can the ancient classification

138
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:07,374
人体体液的古代分类
of the humors in the human body.

139
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:11,708
血液、黑胆汁、黄胆汁和黏液
Blood, black bile, yellow bile, and phlegm.

140
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,250
男性心脏平均重量为何?
Average male heart. Weight?

141
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:18,833
大约255至312公克,父亲
Nine to eleven ounces, Father.

142
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:21,833
女性心脏平均重量为何?
Average female heart. Weight?

143
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:24,583
大约227到283公克
Eight to ten ounces.

144
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:27,000
你觉得是为什么?
Why do you suppose that is?

145
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:29,750
女性心脏质量何以有别?
Difference in mass in female heart?

146
00:13:30,416 --> 00:13:31,666
是情感深度?
Depth of emotion?

147
00:13:32,166 --> 00:13:33,958
还是容易忧郁?
Tendency to the melancholic?

148
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:39,957
父亲,是质量、血容积 肌肉含血量所致
Mass. Volume of blood, Father. Muscular irrigation.

149
00:13:39,958 --> 00:13:43,332
说得对,组织中没有性灵内容
Quite. There is no spiritual content in tissue,

150
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,290
肌肉中也没有情感
and no emotion in a muscle.

151
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:48,875
请描述三尖瓣的主要功能
Now, describe the main function of the tricuspid valve, please.

152
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:54,790
我忘了,父亲,但我一定会想起来
I cannot recall, Father, but I'm sure I will remember.

153
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:56,250
对,你迟早会想起来
Yeah, I'm sure you will.

154
00:13:56,958 --> 00:13:58,999
象牙不会流血,维多
Ivory does not bleed, Victor.

155
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,333
但是人类会
Flesh does.

156
00:14:01,416 --> 00:14:04,415
等你想到一个事实,病人大概断气了
By the time you remember a fact, your patient could be dead.

157
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:05,791
了解吗?
You understand?

158
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:13,333
三尖瓣的主要功能
The main function of the tricuspid valve

159
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,083
是防止血液回流到腔静脉
is to prevent the reflux of blood into the vena cava.

160
00:14:19,708 --> 00:14:22,916
手不行,打不得了
No, not your hands. Not anymore.

161
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:26,708
那是你的医术与意志的工具
They are now the instruments of your craft and will,

162
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:29,083
必须妥善照顾
and we must care for them.

163
00:14:31,875 --> 00:14:34,666
你的脸倒是虚荣的皮相
Your face, however, is vanity.

164
00:14:41,208 --> 00:14:46,833
维多,你继承我的姓氏,以及声誉
You bear my name, Victor, and with it my reputation.

165
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,500
希望你铭记在心
I pray you remember that.

166
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,583
我有预感你拿到好牌,很棒
I feel you have something very good, parce que...

167
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,082
三
Three...

168
00:15:03,083 --> 00:15:04,415
二
Two...

169
00:15:04,416 --> 00:15:05,375
一
One...

170
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:08,541
怎么可能?
That's impossible.

171
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:11,541
我来洗牌
I'll shuffle.

172
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:18,583
母亲?
Mother?
Maman?

173
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:27,999
父亲!
Father!

174
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,416
父亲,妈妈不舒服
Father. It's Mother.

175
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:40,665
我要大量热水和干净麻布,马上去拿
Maman.
I need hot water and clean linen. A lot of it.

176
00:15:40,666 --> 00:15:41,832
- 遵命 - 不,维多!
- Now. - Sir.

177
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:42,833
妈妈?
- No, Victor! - Mother?
- Maman! - Victor!

178
00:15:49,458 --> 00:15:51,999
父亲!
Father! Father!

179
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,541
拜托救救她!
- Victor! - Save her, please!

180
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:41,166
我把母亲视为不可分割的一部分
My mother, whom I had come to consider a part of my very self,

181
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:44,625
我以为她永远不会离去
she who I thought would never leave,

182
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:49,416
她原本还活着...现在却死了
she who was life... was now death.

183
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,916
她眼中的光芒熄灭
Her eyes extinguished,

184
00:16:53,916 --> 00:16:57,125
她的笑容哺育着冰冷大地
her smile feeding the cold earth.

185
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,500
出去!
Leave!

186
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:08,791
全都出去!
All of you, leave!

187
00:17:15,166 --> 00:17:18,125
宇宙有一部分被掏空
A part of the universe had been hollowed out

188
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:22,916
苍穹如今永暗无光
and the firmament was now permanently dark.

189
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:26,083
把眼睛遮起来
Now, cover your eyes.

190
00:17:28,416 --> 00:17:30,833
我叫你看才能看
Don't look until I tell you to.

191
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:33,582
可以了
Now.

192
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:36,832
威廉从小就性情开朗又爱笑
William grew full of sunshine and smiles.

193
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:41,583
他更沉着、温和,更受我父亲的疼爱
He was of a calmer, gentler disposition, clearly favored by my father.

194
00:17:42,291 --> 00:17:43,707
谢谢,父亲
Thank you, Father.

195
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:45,458
不客气,儿子
Oh, it's a pleasure, my boy.

196
00:17:46,791 --> 00:17:49,666
他如同微风,我好似乌云
He was the breeze, I was the storm cloud.

197
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:53,957
他笑容满面,而我愁眉紧锁
He was all laughter, I was all frowns.

198
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:55,083
拿起缰绳
Pick up the reins.

199
00:17:55,625 --> 00:17:58,416
你看我,父亲,看啊
Look at me, Father. Look at me.

200
00:17:59,916 --> 00:18:01,916
生活多了些什么
There was something more.

201
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:05,500
应该说,是少了些什么
Or rather, something was missing.

202
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:09,082
我的母亲一命归西
My mother had died

203
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:12,624
死于当代最负盛名医生之手
at the hands of the most distinguished doctor of his day:

204
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:13,875
也就是我父亲
My father.

205
00:18:14,916 --> 00:18:18,708
一个想法...由心而生
An idea... took shape in my mind.

206
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:21,415
请你定义循环系统
Define the circulatory system, if you will...

207
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:25,040
命中注定,无可避免...
Inevitable, unavoidable...

208
00:18:25,041 --> 00:18:27,957
...说出《心血运动论》中所述内容
...as enunciated in De Motu Cordis.

209
00:18:27,958 --> 00:18:30,041
...直到成真
...until it became truth.

210
00:18:30,625 --> 00:18:31,500
父亲?
Father?

211
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:37,082
你任由她死去,对吧?
You let her die, did you not?

212
00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:41,124
你一定知道,我已尽全力救她了
I did everything in my power to save her. You must know that.

213
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:42,416
所以你失败了
So you failed.

214
00:18:43,375 --> 00:18:45,625
没有人能征服死亡
- No one can conquer death. - Mm-hmm.

215
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:52,541
我会的,我会征服它
I will. I will conquer it.

216
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:57,333
你懂的我都会懂,而且懂更多
Everything you know, I will know. And more.

217
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:01,125
今天的课上得差不多了
I think we've done quite enough for today.

218
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:06,041
我那天晚上脱胎换骨
I was born anew that night.

219
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,291
我见到一个幻觉
I had a vision.

220
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:12,583
我人生头一次看到...
I saw, for the first time...

221
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:15,125
黑暗天使
the Dark Angel.

222
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:30,416
祂答应我一件事
And it made me a promise.

223
00:19:32,208 --> 00:19:35,833
我会拥有控制生死的力量
I would have command over the forces of life and death.

224
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,332
我会成为父亲这种优秀外科医生
I would become every ounce the surgeon my father was.

225
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:43,499
我的野心和影响力将超越他
I would surpass him in ambition and in reach.

226
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:44,875
守护天使...

227
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:46,916
幻觉历历在目
The vision was so clear.

228
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:51,500
比我在清醒或做梦时更清楚
Clearer than anything I'd ever seen in my waking hours or dreams.

229
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:55,916
但怎么可能?
But how?

230
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,708
我很快就遭逢家道中落
My downfall was swift.

231
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:26,040
我母亲的种植园 发生两次造反和一场火灾
Two revolts and a fire on my mother's plantations

232
00:20:26,041 --> 00:20:27,708
家产日益缩水
dwindled the family fortune.

233
00:20:28,375 --> 00:20:31,583
我们保有庄园,但失去了一切
We kept the estate, but lost everything else.

234
00:20:46,083 --> 00:20:49,582
威廉去投靠维也纳的亲戚
William went to one side of the family in Vienna

235
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:51,916
而我先去伦敦,再到爱丁堡
and I to London, then Edinburgh.

236
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:56,625
几十年来,我在那里试图...
And there, for decades, I tried to...

237
00:20:58,875 --> 00:21:02,666
拓展学术界的狭隘局限
expand the narrow limits of academia.

238
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:05,083
生命
Life.

239
00:21:06,625 --> 00:21:10,499
这...就是生命,各位
This... is life, gentlemen.

240
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,707
(1855年,皇家医学院纪律法庭)

241
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:13,958
我们出生
We are born.

242
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:18,416
还来不及站好,就倒下了
Hmm?
And no sooner do we rise, we fall.

243
00:21:19,541 --> 00:21:20,625
死亡
Death.

244
00:21:22,583 --> 00:21:26,040
在站立和倒下之间的空白中
And in the space between that rise and fall,

245
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:27,833
则是我们短浅的见识
our humble little purview.

246
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:31,958
我们控制不了出生
Now, birth is not in our hands.

247
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:34,041
对吧?
Is it?

248
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:40,166
受孕,那道火花,催生出思想与灵魂
Conception, that spark, the animation of thought and soul.

249
00:21:41,208 --> 00:21:42,375
那唯有神能掌控
That is in God's hands.

250
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:44,250
神
God.

251
00:21:45,375 --> 00:21:46,458
但是死亡
But death.

252
00:21:48,083 --> 00:21:49,500
那才是挑战所在
Ah, now there lies the challenge.

253
00:21:50,125 --> 00:21:52,291
也应该是我们关切的重点
That should be our concern.

254
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:54,416
理应如此
It should be.

255
00:21:55,625 --> 00:21:58,875
我们凭什么?我们又不是神,对吧?
Who are we to do so? We are not gods, are we?

256
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:02,790
但如果我们如众神般恣意妄为
But if we are to behave as immodestly as gods,

257
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:05,666
至少我们必能创造出奇迹
we must, at the very least, deliver miracles.

258
00:22:06,166 --> 00:22:07,291
有道理吧?
Wouldn't you say?

259
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:12,499
点燃这些年轻学子心中的神圣火花
Ignite a divine spark...

260
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:15,749
教导他们反抗,而非顺从
...in these young students' minds.
Teach them defiance rather than obedience.

261
00:22:15,750 --> 00:22:21,499
让他们目睹人类可洞悉 大自然的奥秘,阻止死亡
Show that man may pursue nature to her hiding places and stop death.

262
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:24,500
不只是减缓,而是彻底终止!
Not slow it down, but stop it entirely!

263
00:22:30,625 --> 00:22:33,416
安静!
Silence. Silence!

264
00:22:36,958 --> 00:22:42,583
你到底打算怎么传授异想天开之事?
How exactly do you propose to teach what is impossible?

265
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:48,165
复合主题,尸体
Composite subject, the body.

266
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:51,416
那是某店主的尸体 死后不久就送到我这里来
That of a shopkeeper, delivered mere moments after expiration.

267
00:22:51,958 --> 00:22:53,624
外露的大脑功能正常
The brain laid bare but functional,

268
00:22:53,625 --> 00:22:56,540
脊椎分支和迷走神经完好无损
the spinal branches and vagal nerves intact.

269
00:22:56,541 --> 00:22:59,082
你们能看到细如发丝的疤痕
You may observe the hair-thin scars.

270
00:22:59,083 --> 00:23:01,957
靠我的技巧,无需粗陋的缝线
No coarse stitching needed by my own technique.

271
00:23:01,958 --> 00:23:02,999
这只手臂
The arm, you see,

272
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:05,665
来自其他样本,木匠的尸体
comes from another specimen, that of a carpenter.

273
00:23:05,666 --> 00:23:08,875
肌肉、韧带和神经都接起来了
The muscles, ligaments, nerves, all connected now.

274
00:23:30,333 --> 00:23:32,040
电流通过人体会导致
Now, the spasmodic movement of the body

275
00:23:32,041 --> 00:23:34,166
痉挛性运动,这不是新鲜事
caused from the electric current, this is not new.

276
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:37,707
不稀奇,然而能量流通过身体
It's not new. However, the flow of energy through the body

277
00:23:37,708 --> 00:23:39,374
遵循的是截然不同的概念
follows a different notion entirely.

278
00:23:39,375 --> 00:23:41,291
一种称为「气」的东方概念
An Eastern notion called qi.

279
00:23:41,958 --> 00:23:45,124
它顾及体内外的生命能量流
Now, it considers the vital flow of energy both within and without.

280
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:46,874
我利用插入六个穴位的针...
I'm utilizing needles in six--

281
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:51,041
安静!坐下!
Quiet!
Sit down!

282
00:23:52,791 --> 00:23:56,165
这是听证会,博士,不是奇人异士秀
This is a hearing, Doctor, not a carnival act.

283
00:23:56,166 --> 00:23:58,082
你这么做无济于事,维多
You're not helping your cause, Victor.

284
00:23:58,083 --> 00:24:00,749
这种流电骗局唬不了人的
This galvanic trickery will simply not do.

285
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:01,833
骗局
Trickery.

286
00:24:03,791 --> 00:24:04,791
骗局?
Trickery?

287
00:24:07,083 --> 00:24:08,208
你确定?
Are you sure?

288
00:24:13,250 --> 00:24:15,790
那不是骗局,而是决定
That is not trickery. That is a decision.

289
00:24:15,791 --> 00:24:20,249
原分属两具尸体的眼手协调能力
Motor coordination between the eye of one dead man and the arm of another,

290
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:23,665
注入了新意志和基本理解力
infused with a new will and the rudiments of understanding.

291
00:24:23,666 --> 00:24:27,541
死去的脑部有理解力?
Understanding in a brain that already died?

292
00:24:28,583 --> 00:24:29,708
现在放开
Release now.

293
00:24:31,083 --> 00:24:31,916
拜托你
Please.

294
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,708
礼多人不怪嘛
"Please" always helps.

295
00:24:35,916 --> 00:24:39,207
立刻关掉,马上,你这江湖郎中
Turn that off at once. At once, you charlatan.

296
00:24:39,208 --> 00:24:42,165
这是未来和可能实现的事
This is the future. This is possible.

297
00:24:42,166 --> 00:24:44,332
为何不加以研究?将资料数据化?
Why not study it? Why not quantify it?

298
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:50,708
这是邪恶、可憎、猥亵之事!
This is unholy.
An abomination.

299
00:24:51,208 --> 00:24:55,957
生命由神赐予并收回,维多
An obscenity!
God gives life, and God takes it, Victor.

300
00:24:55,958 --> 00:24:58,750
也许神是力有未逮!
Perhaps God is inept!

301
00:24:59,958 --> 00:25:02,374
我们得修正祂的错误!
And it is we that must amend his mistakes!

302
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:05,124
别让这些老蠢材打压你们的想法!
Do not let these old fools extinguish your voice!

303
00:25:05,125 --> 00:25:08,457
要获得答案,唯有不再屈从
The answers only come when coaxed by disobedience,

304
00:25:08,458 --> 00:25:11,416
挣脱恐惧和胆怯的教条!
free of fear and cowardly dogma!

305
00:25:25,916 --> 00:25:27,208
克伦比教授
Professor Krempe.

306
00:26:02,083 --> 00:26:05,874
弗兰肯斯坦男爵 我是海因利奇哈兰德
Baron Frankenstein, my name is Heinrich Harlander,

307
00:26:05,875 --> 00:26:08,749
我带了一封介绍信
and I carry with me a letter of introduction

308
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:10,165
是你弟弟威廉所写的
from your brother, William.

309
00:26:10,166 --> 00:26:11,207
我弟弟?
From my brother?

310
00:26:11,208 --> 00:26:13,707
我请他引荐,盼得与你相识
I asked for the privilege of your acquaintance.

311
00:26:13,708 --> 00:26:15,624
不会占用你太多时间
It won't take but a minute of your time.

312
00:26:15,625 --> 00:26:17,041
- 你先请 - 那好吧
- Please. - Very well.

313
00:26:19,583 --> 00:26:21,750
所以威廉要来看我,对吧?
So William is coming to see me, is that it?

314
00:26:22,458 --> 00:26:24,166
对,几天之后
Yeah, in a matter of days.

315
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:29,166
他想介绍你认识未婚妻 她碰巧是我侄女
He wants to introduce you to his fiancée. My niece, as it happens.

316
00:26:33,458 --> 00:26:36,165
伊莉莎白哈兰德,很出色的年轻女士
Elizabeth Harlander, a very nice young lady,

317
00:26:36,166 --> 00:26:37,583
刚脱离修道院生活不久
fresh from convent life.

318
00:26:38,416 --> 00:26:39,416
这些照片是我拍的
The photographs are mine.

319
00:26:39,958 --> 00:26:43,040
威廉在金融界卓然有成
William has become quite successful in the world of finance.

320
00:26:43,041 --> 00:26:44,874
他打响一己之名号了
He's making a name for himself.

321
00:26:44,875 --> 00:26:47,041
岂有此理!一己之名号?
Ha! A name? For himself?

322
00:26:47,541 --> 00:26:52,583
且不论意愿 只怕这家族名号两兄弟都有份
Well, I'm afraid we both share that name, whether we like it or not.

323
00:26:53,125 --> 00:26:54,999
我拜读过你在《刺胳针》的文章
I read your article in The Lancet.

324
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,875
你真心认为你办得到?
You really believe you can do it?

325
00:26:58,291 --> 00:26:59,375
组出一个人?
Assemble a man?

326
00:27:00,625 --> 00:27:03,500
一整具新身体?赋予它生命?
A full new body? And give it life?

327
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,207
你今天也看到了吧?
You saw it today, didn't you?

328
00:27:06,208 --> 00:27:08,665
其实我只看到你被炮轰得体无完肤
What I saw was a crucifixion, really.

329
00:27:08,666 --> 00:27:11,457
根本来不及说什么就没戏唱了
You were done for before you uttered a word.

330
00:27:11,458 --> 00:27:12,791
我还是让他们看到了
I still showed them.

331
00:27:13,875 --> 00:27:14,707
看到什么?
What?

332
00:27:14,708 --> 00:27:15,666
真相
The truth.

333
00:27:16,458 --> 00:27:18,125
他们晚餐前就会忘得一干二净
They will forget by suppertime.

334
00:27:19,541 --> 00:27:22,000
好啦...那你觉得呢?
Yes, yes, yes. But what did you think? Hmm?

335
00:27:24,083 --> 00:27:25,666
我觉得很高明
I thought it was brilliant.

336
00:27:27,125 --> 00:27:28,207
没错,我也知道
It was. I know.

337
00:27:28,208 --> 00:27:31,082
但你却如孩童般手舞足蹈
But you are like a child, so excited,

338
00:27:31,083 --> 00:27:34,291
紧抓着新宠物不放,结果适得其反
clutching your new pet so tightly that you're strangling it.

339
00:27:35,541 --> 00:27:37,500
所以我才很担心你
That is why I worry about you.

340
00:27:38,708 --> 00:27:41,165
普罗米修斯,你管得住你的火吗?
Can you contain your fire, Prometheus?

341
00:27:41,166 --> 00:27:44,125
还是大功告成前,手就烧焦了?
Or are you going to burn your hands before delivering it?

342
00:27:46,708 --> 00:27:47,583
不无可能
Quite.

343
00:27:48,291 --> 00:27:51,957
恕我直言,但我今天身心具疲
Please do not think me rude, but my day has proven long enough,

344
00:27:51,958 --> 00:27:55,082
实在不宜和陌生人寒暄应酬
and I believe myself totally unfit for the company of strangers.

345
00:27:55,083 --> 00:27:56,665
如果没别的事了...
So if there's nothing more--

346
00:27:56,666 --> 00:27:58,666
但精彩的还在后头
Oh, but there is. Much more.

347
00:28:01,250 --> 00:28:03,707
我已经在爱丁堡找到住所
I've taken quarters in Edinburgh.

348
00:28:03,708 --> 00:28:07,207
三天后,我们跟威廉和伊莉莎白碰面
Three days from now, we are to meet with William and Elizabeth.

349
00:28:07,208 --> 00:28:10,416
那天晚上,我会改变你的命运
And that evening, I will change your destiny.

350
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:14,041
我要让你见识一个不同凡响之物
I will show you something extraordinary.

351
00:28:23,083 --> 00:28:24,500
- 你人真好 - 谢谢,给你

352
00:28:31,458 --> 00:28:35,208
桃子,把桃子转过来,转啊
The peach. The peach. Turn the peach. Turn it.

353
00:28:36,708 --> 00:28:38,333
你又偷吃了
You bit it again.

354
00:28:39,333 --> 00:28:40,833
你吃了桃子
You're eating the peaches.

355
00:28:41,500 --> 00:28:43,333
这个是死亡的象征
This is a memento mori.

356
00:28:44,041 --> 00:28:49,415
桃子则是象征生命和青春 结果被你吃下去?
The peach, symbol of life and youth, and you bite into it?

357
00:28:49,416 --> 00:28:51,707
- 人家饿嘛,奇奇 - 别叫我奇奇
- I was hungry, Kiki. - Don't call me Kiki.

358
00:28:51,708 --> 00:28:53,750
维多弗兰肯斯坦男爵到了,老爷
Baron Victor Frankenstein, sir.

359
00:28:56,041 --> 00:28:56,916
你可以走了
You can leave.

360
00:28:57,708 --> 00:28:58,791
不好意思
Forgive me.

361
00:29:00,333 --> 00:29:01,207
欢迎光临
Welcome.

362
00:29:01,208 --> 00:29:02,291
哈兰德先生
Herr Harlander.

363
00:29:03,250 --> 00:29:05,915
摄影是一门新兴艺术
A young art, photography.

364
00:29:05,916 --> 00:29:07,249
再见,奇奇
Goodbye, Kiki.

365
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:09,208
我已经嗜爱成痴了
Already a passion of mine.

366
00:29:09,708 --> 00:29:11,041
资料带来了吗?
Did you bring the papers?

367
00:29:12,666 --> 00:29:13,625
谢谢
Oh, thank you.

368
00:29:17,333 --> 00:29:19,500
- 你真厉害 - 谢谢
- You're extraordinary. - Thank you.

369
00:29:23,375 --> 00:29:27,625
你要利用神经系统传送能量流
Hmm.
You're using the nervous system to deliver the surge of energy.

370
00:29:28,708 --> 00:29:29,665
对吧?
Are you not?

371
00:29:29,666 --> 00:29:30,915
没错
Correct.

372
00:29:30,916 --> 00:29:34,999
所以你掌控的生命力难以持久
And thus the sustainability of the life force you command

373
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:38,416
会逐渐减弱、消失
is very brief, wanes, evaporates.

374
00:29:40,125 --> 00:29:41,125
何以见得?
How so?

375
00:29:45,083 --> 00:29:48,708
那次解说中 你因自尊心作祟而中断示范
At the lecture, you ended your demonstration out of pride.

376
00:29:51,416 --> 00:29:53,624
但实情是当时的流电生命力
But really, because the galvanic life force

377
00:29:53,625 --> 00:29:55,540
已经变弱了,对吧?
was already fading, was it not?

378
00:29:55,541 --> 00:29:57,208
先生,你是外科医生吗?
Are you yourself a surgeon, sir?

379
00:29:57,708 --> 00:30:00,040
是,陈年往事了,我当过军医
Yeah, once upon a time. An army surgeon.

380
00:30:00,041 --> 00:30:02,707
医术也不怎么高明
Not a particularly skilled one, either.

381
00:30:02,708 --> 00:30:05,957
但我借此奠定了财富基础
But it allowed me to secure the rudiments of my fortune.

382
00:30:05,958 --> 00:30:07,957
我拥有几座兵工厂
I own a few ammunition factories.

383
00:30:07,958 --> 00:30:10,875
- 你是军火商 - 是务实派
- An arms merchant. - A realist.

384
00:30:11,458 --> 00:30:13,332
你知道伊夫林桌吗?
Are you familiar with the Evelyn Tables?

385
00:30:13,333 --> 00:30:15,957
当然,其名来自买家约翰伊夫林爵士
Of course. Acquired by Sir John Evelyn,

386
00:30:15,958 --> 00:30:17,999
一共四张木板,是精密的解剖标本
there are four planks, meticulous dissection,

387
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:20,040
是极早期欧洲文物,呈现了神经
some of the oldest in Europe, presenting the nerves,

388
00:30:20,041 --> 00:30:22,082
血管和尸体动脉,怎么了?
veins and arteries of cadavers. What?

389
00:30:22,083 --> 00:30:24,000
没错,但还有第五张
Yes. But there's a fifth one.

390
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,375
那张最让人拍案叫绝
The most compelling one.

391
00:30:30,458 --> 00:30:33,125
巧夺天工,对吧?
Exquisite, is it not?

392
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:36,583
血肉黏附在木头上
Flesh rendered onto wood.

393
00:30:38,333 --> 00:30:41,582
尸体平放在木板上,剥去层层血肉
The cadaver lies on the plank, is peeled away layer by layer,

394
00:30:41,583 --> 00:30:45,749
用树脂把剩余组织黏在木头上
and the remaining tissue is lacquered with resin onto the wood.

395
00:30:45,750 --> 00:30:48,707
- 这展示了淋巴系统 - 对
- It showcases the lymphatic system. - Yes.

396
00:30:48,708 --> 00:30:52,790
穆斯林医生称为秘密的循环系统
Muslim medics called it the secret circulatory system.

397
00:30:52,791 --> 00:30:58,040
它只输送三公升体液,但网络庞大
It moves a mere three liters of fluid, but it's a vast network.

398
00:30:58,041 --> 00:31:00,000
- 真了不起 - 是啊
- Oh, it's remarkable. - Yes.

399
00:31:01,208 --> 00:31:05,208
对我们和对你来说,关键差异在此
Now for us, for you, the important variation is here.

400
00:31:06,708 --> 00:31:10,290
第九框架,一种非常精细
The ninth configuration. A very delicate,

401
00:31:10,291 --> 00:31:13,749
接近空灵的结构,环绕着心脏
almost ethereal structure surrounding the heart.

402
00:31:13,750 --> 00:31:17,166
它可以分配和储存能量
It can distribute, but also store energy.

403
00:31:21,041 --> 00:31:23,207
对,如果能够启动且不破坏
Yes, if you can access that without destroying

404
00:31:23,208 --> 00:31:25,832
- 周遭的组织... - 错了,不是正面
- the surrounding tissue-- - No. Not through the front.

405
00:31:25,833 --> 00:31:29,291
是背面,脊柱、胸腔弯曲度
The back, spinal column, thoracic curvature.

406
00:31:29,958 --> 00:31:30,832
原来如此
Of course.

407
00:31:30,833 --> 00:31:36,415
超乎想像的能量流、结疤与再生能力
Flow of energy, scarring and regeneration beyond anyone's imagination.

408
00:31:36,416 --> 00:31:37,708
永恒的生命
Life eternal.

409
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:43,041
我愿意提供你无限资源探究永生之道
I will endow your pursuit with unlimited resources.

410
00:31:45,791 --> 00:31:47,250
你要什么回报?
And in exchange?

411
00:31:48,750 --> 00:31:50,208
不用这么直言不讳
No need to become indelicate.

412
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:54,750
我们是寻找真理和超越的志同道合者
We're searchers for truth and transcendence, kindred spirits.

413
00:31:56,416 --> 00:31:58,374
假以时日,我会向你讨个人情
I may in time ask you for a favor in return,

414
00:31:58,375 --> 00:32:02,457
但主要是有幸 为后人记录你的研究过程
but it's mostly the privilege to record your process for posterity.

415
00:32:02,458 --> 00:32:03,708
我不跟人共事
I work alone.

416
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,374
我不会吵到你
I'm very quiet.

417
00:32:06,375 --> 00:32:09,416
哈兰德先生 威廉弗兰肯斯坦和你侄女到了
William Frankenstein and your niece, Herr Harlander.

418
00:32:13,083 --> 00:32:14,208
我会考虑
I shall consider it.

419
00:32:15,541 --> 00:32:16,625
一定会考虑
I'll consider it.

420
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:18,958
男爵
Baron.

421
00:32:20,125 --> 00:32:23,208
此时还故作理智,才真叫人遗憾
Don't pretend to be reasonable now. It would be such a shame.

422
00:32:33,750 --> 00:32:34,957
维多
Victor.

423
00:32:34,958 --> 00:32:36,249
威廉!
William!

424
00:32:36,250 --> 00:32:38,750
- 维多 - 看看你
- Victor. - Look at you.

425
00:32:39,916 --> 00:32:41,624
天啊,你长好大了
My, you've grown.

426
00:32:41,625 --> 00:32:43,333
这我可不敢居功
Through no merit of my own.

427
00:32:44,041 --> 00:32:46,041
介绍你认识我的未婚妻
May I introduce the woman I'm to marry.

428
00:32:46,708 --> 00:32:48,250
伊莉莎白哈兰德小姐
Lady Elizabeth Harlander.

429
00:33:09,666 --> 00:33:11,500
幸会之至
Absolutely delighted.

430
00:33:17,083 --> 00:33:19,333
其实我没那么讶异你被开除
Can't say I was shocked when you were expelled,

431
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:22,582
但他们不留情面地将你扫地出门
but the manner and virulence of your expulsion,

432
00:33:22,583 --> 00:33:23,832
没必要这么绝
uncalled for, I'm sure.

433
00:33:23,833 --> 00:33:24,915
不,有必要
No, it was called for. I earned it.

434
00:33:24,916 --> 00:33:25,833
我是罪有应得

435
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:28,665
我证明了我是罪有应得 哈兰德先生,对吧?
I made it a point to earn it, wouldn't you say, Herr Harlander?

436
00:33:28,666 --> 00:33:30,541
那确实是华丽退场
It was quite an exit, I assure you.

437
00:33:32,416 --> 00:33:33,457
但你何必激怒他们?
Why provoke them?

438
00:33:33,458 --> 00:33:37,874
何不继续低调行事,明哲保身?
Why not just carry on without calling attention to yourself in such a manner?

439
00:33:37,875 --> 00:33:41,624
就算依你的标准也太保守了,威廉
How safe, even by your standards, William.

440
00:33:41,625 --> 00:33:43,458
你的口吻和父亲如出一辙
You almost sound like Father.

441
00:33:44,666 --> 00:33:47,874
我们的父亲最为圆滑得体
He was a most tactful man, our father.

442
00:33:47,875 --> 00:33:50,874
他言行精确、谨慎、不失分寸
He was precise, discreet, measured.

443
00:33:50,875 --> 00:33:55,374
反之,我就不懂谦逊何以是美德
I, on the other hand, fail to see why modesty is considered a virtue at all.

444
00:33:55,375 --> 00:33:57,750
维多一向渴望成为目光焦点
Victor's always been one to harvest attention.

445
00:33:58,416 --> 00:34:01,749
连我小时候也会保持沉默 消消他的气焰
Even as children, I mitigated his voice by staying silent.

446
00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:04,749
也许做得太过火且频繁 维多,你说是吗?
Perhaps too much and far too many times, wouldn't you say, Victor?

447
00:34:04,750 --> 00:34:06,375
如果生命能够再生
If life can be regenerated,

448
00:34:06,958 --> 00:34:08,207
而非只是一种模拟
not as a mere simulation,

449
00:34:08,208 --> 00:34:12,250
而是透过物理、化学方法的神圣行为 何必遮遮掩掩呢?
but as a divine act by physical, chemical means,
why whisper it?

450
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:16,875
你在笑吗?
You laugh?

451
00:34:17,375 --> 00:34:19,707
- 你觉得好笑? - 是的,没错
- You're amused? - I must be, yes.

452
00:34:19,708 --> 00:34:21,165
我的理念没有说清楚吗?
Are my ideas not clear?

453
00:34:21,166 --> 00:34:23,790
你是讲得很理直气壮
You certainly expressed them loudly enough.

454
00:34:23,791 --> 00:34:25,124
你觉得一无是处?
Are they not worthwhile?

455
00:34:25,125 --> 00:34:27,833
理念本身不会一无是处
Ideas are not worthwhile by themselves, I don't believe.

456
00:34:30,291 --> 00:34:32,082
愿闻其详
Enlighten me, please.

457
00:34:32,083 --> 00:34:34,374
就拿战争来说吧
Take the war, for example.

458
00:34:34,375 --> 00:34:37,083
威廉,到我书房享用雪茄和白兰地?
William, cigar and brandy in my study?

459
00:34:37,583 --> 00:34:41,291
你肯定听过我侄女发表过相关高见
Surely you've heard my niece expound on the matter before.

460
00:34:42,416 --> 00:34:43,458
我们先失陪了
You'll excuse us.

461
00:34:48,291 --> 00:34:50,541
好极了,请说,理念
Pray, carry on. Ideas.

462
00:34:51,458 --> 00:34:57,416
这个嘛...荣誉、国家、勇气
Well... honor, country, valor.

463
00:34:58,625 --> 00:35:01,707
这些崇高理念无疑有其价值
These surely are worthwhile, elevated ideas by themselves,

464
00:35:01,708 --> 00:35:02,875
你同意吧?
wouldn't you agree?

465
00:35:04,291 --> 00:35:06,375
只是男人却为了它们而送命
- Mm-hmm. - And nevertheless, men are dying for them.

466
00:35:07,041 --> 00:35:08,957
死法绝不崇高
In a decidedly un-elevated way,

467
00:35:08,958 --> 00:35:11,915
脸伏泥浆、血水呛喉
face down in the mud, choking on blood,

468
00:35:11,916 --> 00:35:13,208
痛苦惨叫
screaming in pain.

469
00:35:14,208 --> 00:35:17,499
他们曾是某人的父亲、兄弟或儿子
Men that were fathers, brothers or sons to someone out there.

470
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:19,374
这些男儿曾被母亲喂养、清洗和抚育
Men that were fed, cleaned and nursed

471
00:35:19,375 --> 00:35:21,375
并教导他们认识这个世界
and schooled into this world by their mothers,

472
00:35:21,916 --> 00:35:23,749
结果却命丧于远方沙场
only to fall on a battlefield far away,

473
00:35:23,750 --> 00:35:26,166
造成这些悲剧的政客却远在天边
far from those that provoke these tragedies.

474
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:31,458
他们安心在家,避开鲜血或刺刀
Those men remain at home, untouched by blood or bayonet,

475
00:35:32,416 --> 00:35:35,458
皮肉具全,身覆洁暖的毛毯
their skin unpierced, their blankets warm and clean.

476
00:35:38,125 --> 00:35:40,874
这就是蠢材追求理念的下场
That is what happens when ideas are pursued by fools.

477
00:35:40,875 --> 00:35:42,708
你认为我是蠢材?
And you think me a fool?
Hmm?

478
00:35:46,333 --> 00:35:47,916
快去享用你的白兰地和雪茄吧
Run to your brandy and cigars.

479
00:35:48,625 --> 00:35:49,958
他们在等你
The boys are waiting.

480
00:35:56,333 --> 00:36:01,166
人多少次以为碰见天使或恶魔
How often a man believes he's met an angel or a devil,

481
00:36:02,708 --> 00:36:04,958
结果只是幻梦一场
only to find it is all an illusion.

482
00:36:07,958 --> 00:36:09,750
我们所下的这盘棋
The game of chess we play...

483
00:36:11,166 --> 00:36:13,000
只是在跟自己较量罢了
we play only against ourselves.

484
00:36:15,166 --> 00:36:16,166
帮帮他
Help him.

485
00:36:16,708 --> 00:36:17,625
帮帮他!
Help him!

486
00:36:18,791 --> 00:36:20,541
来,喝一点
Here you go. Drink some.

487
00:36:43,208 --> 00:36:44,958
你最好跟我来
You better come with me.

488
00:36:45,875 --> 00:36:47,290
没东西啊
Nothing.

489
00:36:47,291 --> 00:36:48,958
船长,值班船员看到牠了
Sir, the watchman saw him.

490
00:36:49,791 --> 00:36:51,457
牠在迷雾中绕着船走
Circling the ship. In the mist.

491
00:36:51,458 --> 00:36:53,165
我们都看到牠淹死了
We all saw him drown.

492
00:36:53,166 --> 00:36:54,415
船长
Sir.

493
00:36:54,416 --> 00:36:56,124
大伙们都吓坏了
The men are terrified.

494
00:36:56,125 --> 00:36:58,457
他们认为应该把那个人留在冰原上
They think that man should be surrendered to the ice

495
00:36:58,458 --> 00:36:59,708
了结此事
and be done with this.

496
00:37:02,333 --> 00:37:04,458
他受我保护...
He is under my protection...

497
00:37:06,541 --> 00:37:08,458
国王也为他撑腰!
and the protection of the Crown!

498
00:37:21,833 --> 00:37:24,832
几周后,我跟威廉、哈兰德同行
A few weeks later, I rode with William and Harlander

499
00:37:24,833 --> 00:37:27,457
越过水道,前往瓦都兹附近一座湖
to a lake near Vaduz across the channel.

500
00:37:27,458 --> 00:37:31,040
那座塔楼是建来灌溉田地的过滤水厂
The tower was built as a water filtration plant to irrigate the fields.

501
00:37:31,041 --> 00:37:34,083
一开战,这个公共建案就停工了
Public works, so construction was abandoned at the start of the war.

502
00:37:35,125 --> 00:37:37,499
不是这场战争,是之前那场
Not this war, the one before.

503
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:39,708
或是再前一场,我记不清楚了
Or the one before that, I cannot quite remember.

504
00:37:44,541 --> 00:37:46,541
当我一看到它...
The moment I laid eyes on it...

505
00:37:47,708 --> 00:37:48,666
那座塔楼
The tower.

506
00:37:49,375 --> 00:37:52,916
我感受到命运的呼唤
I could feel destiny calling.

507
00:38:03,750 --> 00:38:05,665
建物大致上完好无损
The structure's basically intact.

508
00:38:05,666 --> 00:38:08,791
这里还有个从屋顶直通底部的通道
And there's a chute going from top, right to the bottom.

509
00:38:09,416 --> 00:38:11,165
我会妥善收拾你的家当
I can arrange for your belongings.

510
00:38:11,166 --> 00:38:13,125
请人从爱丁堡运送过来
We'll bring them from Edinburgh.

511
00:38:26,958 --> 00:38:29,958
我会满足你一切需求
Anything you need or want shall be granted.

512
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:32,625
- 一切需求? - 正是
- Anything? - Anything.

513
00:38:41,833 --> 00:38:45,374
我已委托威廉包办 研究期间的相关事宜
I have secured William's service for the duration of the project.

514
00:38:45,375 --> 00:38:47,041
我需要一间牢房
I'll need a holding cell.

515
00:38:47,625 --> 00:38:49,541
- 和一间冷冻室,都要紧邻实验室 - 威廉
- And an ice chamber close to the lab. - William.

516
00:38:50,458 --> 00:38:52,790
塔楼底部有两座泵浦蓄水池
There are two pump reservoirs at the base of the tower.

517
00:38:52,791 --> 00:38:54,290
我们会进行翻修
We'll repurpose those.

518
00:38:54,291 --> 00:38:56,207
我们得修理蒸气机
We shall need to recondition the steam engines.

519
00:38:56,208 --> 00:38:58,165
需要充分燃料确保正常运转
We'll need enough fuel to make sure they run.

520
00:38:58,166 --> 00:39:02,207
那两处要安装四个高容量伏特电池
There and there, four high-capacity voltaic batteries,

521
00:39:02,208 --> 00:39:04,082
正极和负极
positive and negative polarity,

522
00:39:04,083 --> 00:39:08,457
还要一组纯银的避雷针系统 能往下伸进实验室
and a lightning rod system of pure silver telescoping down into the lab.

523
00:39:08,458 --> 00:39:13,791
好,我的承包商 能制造出你要的各种设备
Yes. My contractors can manufacture any and all equipment you may require.

524
00:39:15,708 --> 00:39:19,250
那我们应该达成共识啰?
I take it then that we have an understanding?

525
00:39:25,250 --> 00:39:26,791
那就一言为定
A bargain has been struck.

526
00:39:37,333 --> 00:39:38,333
混蛋!
Bastard!

527
00:39:40,166 --> 00:39:41,208
这个不行
No. No. Not this one.

528
00:39:45,375 --> 00:39:46,291
张开嘴巴
Aah. Open your mouth.

529
00:39:48,541 --> 00:39:51,665
幸亏你快被绞死,不死也活不过一年
You, you're lucky to be hanged. You would have died within the year.

530
00:39:51,666 --> 00:39:54,165
哈兰德先生答应我可以取得最佳样本
Herr Harlander promised me access to optimal specimens.

531
00:39:54,166 --> 00:39:56,040
也许是吧,爵爷
Yeah, that he may have, your lordship,

532
00:39:56,041 --> 00:39:57,458
但你也知道
but as you well know,

533
00:39:58,458 --> 00:40:00,874
犯罪得不偿失,在此尤为明证
crime doesn't pay, and it's a poor showing of it we have here.

534
00:40:00,875 --> 00:40:02,665
他们全都是可怜的败类
They're wretches every one of them.

535
00:40:02,666 --> 00:40:04,000
我深表遗憾
I'm sorry about that.

536
00:40:04,708 --> 00:40:06,166
他背部很强壮,这个可以
That's a strong back. This one will do.

537
00:40:42,291 --> 00:40:43,332
稍后再来
Come back later.

538
00:40:43,333 --> 00:40:44,500
告解?
Confession?

539
00:40:46,166 --> 00:40:48,041
这下我好奇了
I was intrigued.

540
00:40:50,500 --> 00:40:54,791
那个纤细、虔诚的尤物要告解什么?
What would such a delicate, pious creature have to confess to?

541
00:40:57,166 --> 00:41:00,540
所幸的是,天赐良机
As luck would have it, an opportunity presented itself,

542
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:01,666
而我...
and I...

543
00:41:04,041 --> 00:41:05,666
我即将得知真相
I was about to find out.

544
00:41:26,916 --> 00:41:28,750
神父,请赦免我的罪
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

545
00:41:29,708 --> 00:41:33,290
你上次是何时告解,孩子?
How long has it been
since your last confession, my daughter?

546
00:41:33,291 --> 00:41:35,583
不到一周前,神父,我当时在修道院
Barely a week, Father. I was in a convent.

547
00:41:36,083 --> 00:41:37,166
才一周?
A week?

548
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:40,624
你这么快就犯了罪?
Tsk-tsk. Have you so hastily committed sin?

549
00:41:40,625 --> 00:41:41,541
是的
I have.

550
00:41:42,125 --> 00:41:43,958
是想法,不是行为
Sin of intent, not deed.

551
00:41:44,625 --> 00:41:46,624
- 跟男人有关吧? - 是的
- A man, is it? - Yes.

552
00:41:46,625 --> 00:41:48,000
我未婚夫的哥哥
My fiancé's brother.

553
00:41:49,541 --> 00:41:50,707
是色欲?
Lust?

554
00:41:50,708 --> 00:41:51,624
是憎恶
Hatred...

555
00:41:51,625 --> 00:41:52,541
憎恶...

556
00:41:53,500 --> 00:41:56,666
- 憎恶? - 他言行低俗、荒诞
- Hatred? - The man is appalling, grotesque.

557
00:41:57,916 --> 00:41:59,332
话说得真重
Harsh words.

558
00:41:59,333 --> 00:42:00,915
相当不近人情,对吧?
Rather uncharitable, wouldn't you say?

559
00:42:00,916 --> 00:42:03,582
恕我直言,神父,你不认识对方
Respectfully, Father, you do not know this man.

560
00:42:03,583 --> 00:42:07,124
他想操控身边一切的人事物
He tries to control and manipulate everything and everyone around him.

561
00:42:07,125 --> 00:42:09,874
他如同暴君,就爱以受害者自居
Like every tyrant, he delights in playing the victim.

562
00:42:09,875 --> 00:42:11,332
我会说,他唯一的可取之处
His only advantage, I would say,

563
00:42:11,333 --> 00:42:13,958
是他比他自认的更加大意
is he's far cruder than he believes himself to be.

564
00:42:14,916 --> 00:42:15,916
大意?
Cruder?

565
00:42:16,750 --> 00:42:18,249
请说明一下,孩子
Uh, pray explain yourself, my child.

566
00:42:18,250 --> 00:42:21,125
首先,要发现他很简单
For one, he's easy to spot.

567
00:42:22,041 --> 00:42:26,333
连在赶集日的热闹街道上 也能轻易认出他
You can see him... even on a busy street on market day.

568
00:42:32,375 --> 00:42:33,915
说吧,你多早就看到我了?
Tell me, how soon did you spot me?

569
00:42:33,916 --> 00:42:36,999
你还没看到我,我就看到你了 我话就说到这边
I saw you well before you saw me, I can say that much.

570
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:37,915
你用餐了吗?
Have you had supper?

571
00:42:37,916 --> 00:42:40,040
我没那么饿,男爵,谢谢
I'm not that hungry, Baron. Thank you.

572
00:42:40,041 --> 00:42:41,916
我可是饿坏了
Well, I for one am famished.

573
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:46,582
- 谢谢你,大好人 - 谢谢
- Thank you, my good man. - Thank you, sir.

574
00:42:46,583 --> 00:42:49,375
你买了什么书?能看看吗?
What books did you buy, hmm? May I?

575
00:42:50,166 --> 00:42:51,166
猜猜看
Guess.

576
00:42:51,750 --> 00:42:53,290
- 猜? - 我要你用猜的
- Guess? - Mm-hmm. I'd rather that you did.

577
00:42:53,291 --> 00:42:54,333
那好吧
Very well.

578
00:42:58,083 --> 00:42:59,291
是罗曼史...
A romance...

579
00:42:59,958 --> 00:43:04,082
充斥着地中海阳光、绮罗与情爱纠葛
drenched in Mediterranean sun and silk and the skirmishes of love.

580
00:43:04,083 --> 00:43:06,833
狗眼看人低,但意料之中
Insulting, but unsurprising.

581
00:43:07,833 --> 00:43:08,833
是吗?
Really?

582
00:43:15,166 --> 00:43:16,291
昆虫?
- Insects? - Mm.

583
00:43:17,708 --> 00:43:20,583
我的科学喜好偏向微小生物
My interest in science leans towards the smallest things.

584
00:43:21,250 --> 00:43:24,166
随着大自然或是神的节奏而律动
Moving with nature, perhaps the rhythms of God.

585
00:43:25,166 --> 00:43:29,458
我经常在寻找更纯粹、惊奇的事物
I've always searched for something more pure, marvelous.

586
00:43:33,166 --> 00:43:35,375
你是在修道院寻找这个?
Is that what you were seeking in the convent?

587
00:43:37,958 --> 00:43:39,000
算是吧
In a way.

588
00:43:41,166 --> 00:43:42,166
值得吗?
Was it worth it?

589
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:45,000
有任何事值得吗?
Is anything?

590
00:43:54,166 --> 00:43:56,000
请与我共舞,弟媳
Permit me, sister.

591
00:44:00,208 --> 00:44:01,625
此举不甚得体
This hardly seems appropriate.

592
00:44:02,250 --> 00:44:03,291
有任何事得体吗?
Is anything?

593
00:44:07,791 --> 00:44:08,833
好极了
Very well.

594
00:44:19,416 --> 00:44:20,625
你笑了!
Laughter!

595
00:44:23,041 --> 00:44:24,666
史无前例
And for the very first time,

596
00:44:25,541 --> 00:44:27,666
我变得更关注生命
I became more interested in life

597
00:44:28,250 --> 00:44:31,457
反而没那么在乎...
and somewhat less interested in death.

598
00:44:31,458 --> 00:44:32,583
死亡

599
00:44:50,916 --> 00:44:55,333
主针有一套快速的螺栓系统
The main rod has a fast bolting system.

600
00:44:56,041 --> 00:44:57,375
你有使用合金吗?
Did you use an alloy?

601
00:44:58,333 --> 00:44:59,874
我用了铜和锌
Copper and zinc.

602
00:44:59,875 --> 00:45:02,791
这...这样行不通,重做
This is... This simply will not do. Start over.

603
00:45:03,458 --> 00:45:05,958
纯银是绝佳导体
Pure silver is a perfect conductor.

604
00:45:06,958 --> 00:45:09,124
威廉,你得留下来监工,拜托
William, you must stay behind. Please.

605
00:45:09,125 --> 00:45:11,124
我只信得过你
I trust you above anyone else.

606
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:12,458
再几天就好了
Only for a few more days.

607
00:45:20,708 --> 00:45:22,583
你抓不到的
You're not going to catch her.

608
00:45:27,958 --> 00:45:28,916
好漂亮
Beautiful. Beautiful.

609
00:45:30,625 --> 00:45:32,832
要关起来还是放走?
- Should we trap her or let her go? - Mm...

610
00:45:32,833 --> 00:45:33,791
关起来
Trap her.

611
00:45:36,541 --> 00:45:38,250
我们总算有共通点了
Now we have something in common.

612
00:45:39,833 --> 00:45:40,833
你的囚犯
A prisoner.

613
00:45:41,333 --> 00:45:46,291
如先前约定 威廉负责兴建实验室和提供所需
As promised, William took dutiful charge of the laboratory build and needs.

614
00:45:48,416 --> 00:45:50,374
请帮我修那里
Can you fix that over there, please?

615
00:45:50,375 --> 00:45:51,458
去帮忙
Go, help.

616
00:45:52,458 --> 00:45:55,458
他完全依照我的指示行事
He followed my instructions to the letter.

617
00:45:57,750 --> 00:45:58,833
电池
The battery.

618
00:46:07,500 --> 00:46:09,083
现在都是纯银了
It's all pure silver now.

619
00:46:09,708 --> 00:46:13,500
对应淋巴系统的传导点
Conduction points corresponding to the lymphatic system,

620
00:46:14,291 --> 00:46:18,166
做法错综复杂,但我搞定了
which was quite complex.
- But I managed. - Mm-hmm.

621
00:46:59,833 --> 00:47:03,165
哈兰德先生,谢谢,很愉快的宴会
Herr Harlander, thank you. The party's delightful.

622
00:47:03,166 --> 00:47:06,416
希望我们没有打断你做研究
I hope we're not distracting you from your research

623
00:47:07,666 --> 00:47:09,833
害你要分心照顾我和伊莉莎白
to tend to me and Elizabeth.

624
00:47:11,583 --> 00:47:12,499
完全没有
Not at all.

625
00:47:12,500 --> 00:47:16,041
她还年轻,可以依靠我们保护她
She's young. She can count on us to guard her.

626
00:47:19,791 --> 00:47:21,707
我就不打扰你了
I shall leave you your privacy.

627
00:47:21,708 --> 00:47:24,083
我们之间无需托辞
No need for subterfuge between us.

628
00:47:26,166 --> 00:47:29,583
法国马桶,如厕时响起涓涓细流声
French porcelain, chimes to a man's stream.

629
00:47:31,166 --> 00:47:35,415
我快找到怎么进入淋巴系统的解方了
I am very near a solution, an access point to the lymphatic system.

630
00:47:35,416 --> 00:47:37,208
是啊,那件事
Ah, yeah, that.

631
00:47:38,125 --> 00:47:39,291
已经过好久了
It's been so long.

632
00:47:41,583 --> 00:47:43,291
战事渐缓
The war is waning.

633
00:47:45,083 --> 00:47:47,207
我的资助会随战争而结束
And my funding will end with it.

634
00:47:47,208 --> 00:47:49,749
你说过你会提供无限资助
You said your funds were unlimited.

635
00:47:49,750 --> 00:47:51,166
可是我的耐心有限
My patience is not.

636
00:47:52,083 --> 00:47:55,791
我收到可靠消息 一周内将爆发一场战役
I have it on good authority that a battle is to take place within a week.

637
00:47:57,833 --> 00:48:00,999
战争狂潮会让我们渔翁得利
The tide of war will deliver its bounty to our shore.

638
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:03,499
战场?但是尸体会严重受损
A battlefield? The bodies will be mangled.

639
00:48:03,500 --> 00:48:04,500
一周
One week.

640
00:48:05,166 --> 00:48:06,707
- 一周? - 一周后
- One week? - After that, history will pass us by.

641
00:48:06,708 --> 00:48:08,291
历史会弃我们而去

642
00:48:10,708 --> 00:48:13,125
男爵,帮我冲水好吗?
Flush that for me, will you, Baron?

643
00:48:15,583 --> 00:48:19,540
一周就要决定传送电流的方法
A week to determine how to deliver the current.

644
00:48:19,541 --> 00:48:20,458
根本做梦
Impossible.

645
00:48:21,625 --> 00:48:22,874
我该怎么办?
What would I do?

646
00:48:22,875 --> 00:48:24,791
我知道我只差临门一脚
I was close. I could feel it.

647
00:48:25,625 --> 00:48:29,541
然后...人生从中作梗
And then...
life got in the way.

648
00:48:32,500 --> 00:48:33,916
牠很想念你
Oh.
I believe she missed you.

649
00:48:35,416 --> 00:48:37,790
我得警告你,我一直在进行解剖研究
I must warn you, Elizabeth,

650
00:48:37,791 --> 00:48:39,083
美极了
- I've been working on a dissection. - It's beautiful.

651
00:48:41,916 --> 00:48:43,000
你有吓到吗?
Does it shock you?

652
00:48:43,833 --> 00:48:46,291
这让我想起了殉道画
Reminds me of martyrdom paintings.

653
00:48:49,750 --> 00:48:50,666
痛苦消逝
Pain is gone.

654
00:48:52,166 --> 00:48:55,416
神的巧思展现在对称和形体中
You can see God's design in the symmetry and the shapes.

655
00:48:57,833 --> 00:48:58,791
伊莉莎白
Elizabeth.

656
00:49:00,833 --> 00:49:02,625
我得对你坦白一件事
I must confess something to you.

657
00:49:04,541 --> 00:49:07,625
我和你都相信惊奇事物
I have a belief in the marvelous and so do you.

658
00:49:09,666 --> 00:49:12,040
我们心灵相系,你是否感同身受?
There is a bond between us. Can you feel it?

659
00:49:12,041 --> 00:49:16,083
那连结几乎具体可见 我深信那另有所指
An almost physical one. I truly believe it to be something else.

660
00:49:24,083 --> 00:49:26,958
相信不代表是事实
Believing something does not make it true.

661
00:49:30,416 --> 00:49:31,625
那你为什么来这里?
Then why are you here?

662
00:49:39,208 --> 00:49:41,291
牠是个美丽的生物,对吧?
Beautiful creature, is she not?

663
00:49:43,125 --> 00:49:47,625
脱俗、迷人至极,却又如此奇特
Remote. Entirely bewitching, but so odd.

664
00:49:53,125 --> 00:49:54,208
牠有三颗心脏
Three hearts.

665
00:49:55,166 --> 00:49:57,166
复眼、白色血液
Multiple eyes. White blood.

666
00:49:59,041 --> 00:50:01,416
妙的是,牠毫无选择
And a fascinating lack of choice.

667
00:50:01,958 --> 00:50:03,125
我不懂
I don't understand.

668
00:50:04,500 --> 00:50:06,375
选择是灵魂的所在
Choice is the seat of the soul.

669
00:50:09,083 --> 00:50:11,000
神赐给我们的礼物
The one gift God granted us.

670
00:50:16,166 --> 00:50:17,250
伊莉莎白...
Elizabeth...

671
00:50:21,583 --> 00:50:22,957
我已作出抉择
I have chosen.

672
00:50:22,958 --> 00:50:24,125
晚安
Good night.

673
00:50:30,833 --> 00:50:31,791
伊莉莎白!
Elizabeth!

674
00:50:35,041 --> 00:50:36,333
伊莉莎白!
Elizabeth!

675
00:50:40,376 --> 00:50:41,750
我以为我失败了
I thought I had failed.

676
00:50:43,333 --> 00:50:44,482
我以为彻底结束了
I thought it was entirely over. 

677
00:50:44,482 --> 00:50:45,186
我以为...
I thought...

678
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:47,757
我以为...
And I thought...

679
00:50:49,208 --> 00:50:49,933
我...
And I...

680
00:50:51,056 --> 00:50:52,080
对称
The symmetry.

681
00:50:58,719 --> 00:50:59,889
神的对称
God's symmetry. 

682
00:50:59,889 --> 00:51:00,794
我想通了
Yes, yes.

683
00:51:14,166 --> 00:51:14,760
这就对了
Yes.

684
00:51:29,333 --> 00:51:31,625
把电池放在淋巴系统上
Placing the battery above the lymphatic system.

685
00:51:32,162 --> 00:51:33,873
我找到关键了
I had found the key.

686
00:51:34,534 --> 00:51:36,582
这下什么都阻止不了我
Nothing could stop me now.

687
00:51:38,605 --> 00:51:39,437
势不可挡
Nothing.

688
00:51:42,500 --> 00:51:43,381
不行
No! 

689
00:51:43,381 --> 00:51:44,683
除非我有标示
No, do not take any bodies

690
00:51:44,683 --> 00:51:47,672
否则别搬最上层或底部的尸体
from the top or the bottom of the pile unless I mark them.

691
00:51:48,013 --> 00:51:50,250
组织可能冻坏或腐败了
Ice or rot may have destroyed the tissue.

692
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:52,208
找中间的尸体就好
Look only in the middle.

693
00:51:58,750 --> 00:52:00,711
不缩小范围
Abundance can be disorienting 

694
00:52:00,711 --> 00:52:02,690
根本无从找起
unless one hones one's aim.

695
00:52:02,690 --> 00:52:04,473
我喜欢个头高的样本
I'm favoring tall specimens, 

696
00:52:04,473 --> 00:52:05,626
四肢要长
long limbs.

697
00:52:05,626 --> 00:52:07,416
大块头进行起来更容易
Scale will make the work easier.

698
00:52:07,416 --> 00:52:08,375
我喜欢
I like that.

699
00:52:10,321 --> 00:52:11,153
很好
Perfection.

700
00:52:12,416 --> 00:52:13,170
有何不可呢
And why not, 

701
00:52:13,551 --> 00:52:14,333
亲爱的男爵
dear Baron?

702
00:52:15,875 --> 00:52:17,079
确实 有何不可
Indeed, why not?

703
00:52:17,618 --> 00:52:19,416
找一颗完整的头颅
Look for a head that's intact.

704
00:52:20,916 --> 00:52:21,875
把那具搬上车
Put that one in the cart.

705
00:52:27,208 --> 00:52:28,416
把那具放在那里
Set that one over there.

706
00:52:28,916 --> 00:52:29,958
把其他的搬进来
Bring the others.

707
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:36,916
老天
Oh, good God.

708
00:53:50,872 --> 00:53:51,626
让一让好吗?
Do you mind?

709
00:55:19,291 --> 00:55:20,572
完成了
It is finished.

710
00:56:05,625 --> 00:56:06,833
哈兰德先生!
Herr Harlander!

711
00:56:07,958 --> 00:56:09,250
风暴要来了!
A storm is coming!

712
00:56:12,166 --> 00:56:13,000
我的手杖
My cane.

713
00:56:14,541 --> 00:56:15,707
我的手杖!
My cane!

714
00:56:15,708 --> 00:56:17,125
放在我手杖的把手里面
My cane, in the handle.

715
00:56:26,833 --> 00:56:28,124
是水银
Mercury.

716
00:56:28,125 --> 00:56:29,875
- 你生病了吗? - 谢谢
- Are you ill? - Thank you.

717
00:56:40,833 --> 00:56:42,875
那是...梅毒吗?
Is it... syphilis?

718
00:56:45,541 --> 00:56:46,708
对,我快死了
Yeah, I'm dying.

719
00:56:48,833 --> 00:56:51,832
同维纳斯春风一夜,和水银厮守一生
One night with Venus, a lifetime with Mercury.

720
00:56:51,833 --> 00:56:52,958
俗语是这么说的吧?
Isn't that the phrase?

721
00:56:53,708 --> 00:56:54,749
你是第几期?
What stage?

722
00:56:54,750 --> 00:56:55,665
第二期?
Secondary?

723
00:56:55,666 --> 00:56:58,124
我俩都知道确切的病程
We both know the precise schedule.

724
00:56:58,125 --> 00:57:00,665
它开始啃食我的骨头
It starts to eat away my bones,

725
00:57:00,666 --> 00:57:06,374
眼眶、脸颊、牙齿、下巴、头颅 暴露出我的大脑
orbital, cheek, teeth, jaw, skull, exposing my brain.

726
00:57:06,375 --> 00:57:10,208
肿瘤、发狂、痛不欲生
Tumors, madness, excruciating pain.

727
00:57:11,416 --> 00:57:16,083
有天早上,我会开始尖叫,停不下来
One fine morning,
I will start to scream and I will never stop.

728
00:57:16,833 --> 00:57:20,415
我难以面对如此下流的死法
I cannot face such a vulgar demise.

729
00:57:20,416 --> 00:57:23,124
所以我得提起那个条件
Which brings me to my one condition.

730
